Chelsea winger, Callum Hudson-Odoi has provided the latest update on his health condition after he contracted Coronavirus. DAILY POST had reported last Thursday that the 19-year-old tested positive for COVID-19. Hudson-Odoi has now revealed he is feeling well and recovered from the virus symptoms. Providing an update on his condition, Hudson-Odoi, in a video posted on his official Instagram page at the weekend said: “Hi guys. As you may be aware, I had the virus for the last couple of days, which I have recovered from. “I am following the health guidelines and self-isolating myself from everybody for the week. “I hope to see everybody soon and hopefully be back on the pitch very soon. Take care.” Coronavirus, also known as COVID-19, has become a global problem with Europe now at the centre of the outbreak. Major sporting activities has now been put on hold in a bid to prevent the spread of the dreaded disease. The World Health Organisation, WHO, has since declared coronavirus a global pandemic.